# Build & Package — DLLs into pyRevit Extension

## Build Matrix (Hard Rule)

Always produce BOTH targets:

| Target Framework | Revit Versions |
|------------------|----------------|
| `net48` | 2023–2024 |
| `net8.0-windows` | 2025–2026 |

## Packaging (Copy Step)

Copy outputs to pyRevit extension lib folders:

```
<Ext>.extension/
  lib/
    net48/    # dll + all dependencies for Revit 2023–2024
    net8/     # dll + all dependencies for Revit 2025–2026
```

## Dependency Rule

If DLL has dependencies, place them alongside the DLL in the same lib folder.

```
lib/net48/
  YourDll.dll
  Newtonsoft.Json.dll   # dependency
  OtherLib.dll          # dependency
```

## Never Do

- Do NOT ship separate `.addin` manifests for this workflow.
- Do NOT point pyRevit to `bin/Debug` or `bin/Release` paths in production builds.
- Do NOT assume dependencies are shared — each lib folder must be self-contained.
